\b Getting started
\b0 \
The module is initially created with 2 steps, but you can add as many as you need using the add (
\b a
\b0 ) button. \
If you want the action sequencer to carry out a set of actions immediately when started then set all step times to 0 min 0 secs. Otherwise set the time for each step.\
If you want to put step times in beats and bars then set the correct BPM and Beats per bar first.\
Choose the module before selecting its action.\
Use the copy and paste buttons to copy action settings between steps. 
\i\b \
\

\i0 Editing the step time (mins/secs/bars/beats)\

\b0 After you change the step time of any step, all steps are resorted to be in time order. This may mean that the step you are editing moves to a new position when you enter its step time; its step number will also change. (Note - it's step ID will always remain the same).\
