\b Using action  "Jump to step ID" for jumping and looping\

\b0 The Action Sequencer module has an action called "Jump to step ID" that will cause the sequencer to immediately jump to another step. This can be useful for looping a sequence or branching to a different step. \
To make the sequence loop to the start when it reaches its last step: add a new step at the end of the sequence with the current Action Sequencer module selected in the "module" box, and "jump to step ID" selected in the "action" box.  \
Put the step ID of the step 1 into the value settings number box - or use the slider to select the correct ID. \
Make sure that step you are jumping back to has an earlier step time than the step your jumping from (see note below).\

\b N.B. 
\b0  Using the  "Jump to step ID"  action, it is possible that the action sequencer can go into an 
\b endless loop
\b0 . This will only happen if the step you are jumping to is before the current step and has the same step time. If you're looping back, make sure it is to an earlier step time.  (If you do this by mistake, an automatic delay of 1/10 sec will be added between each step to stop this crashing your computer).\
